## Usage

Once installed, this addon automatically runs hooks when Claude Code uses tools.

## Configuration

Edit `addon.toml` to configure hooks and behavior:

```toml
[addon]
name = "{{name}}"
version = "1.0.0"

[hooks]
PreToolUse = [
  { matcher = "Bash", handler = "./hook.ts", priority = 0 }
]
```

### Hook Matchers

- `"Bash"` - Match Bash tool calls
- `"Read"` - Match file read operations
- `"Write"` - Match file write operations
- `"*"` - Match all tools

### Priority

Higher priority hooks run first. Use priority to control execution order when multiple addons are installed.

## Development

### Hook Exit Codes

- `0` - Allow the tool call to proceed
- `1` - Error (stop execution with error message)
- `2` - Block (skip this tool call silently)

### Testing

Test your hook locally:

```bash
echo '{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_input":{"command":"ls"}}' | bun run hook.ts
```

